claim.claim-text:
5. A method of creating a fading color hue in a cover, which includes a frame and a lens, for a portable communication device, the method comprising: 
creating a polished region on one surface region of the lens to allow for maximum transfer of light emerging from the frame; 
creating a reflective region on another surface region of the lens to allow for maximum reflection of light emerging from the frame; 
creating a dispersion region on a third surface region of the lens, wherein the third surface region is positioned opposite the reflective region; and 
securing the lens to the frame, such that the polished region and the reflective region are in close proximate to the frame to allow light to emerge form the frame and enter the lens thereby creating a gradually fading hue in the lens in the third surface region.
